Zoe I think you are finding squats hard because your technique is a little bit off! Try hingeing your bum out first, bending at your hips before you lower into a squat and keep your weight in your heels so you don't hurt your knees! Focus on pulling your bum down rather than bending your knees too much! Your weight should be in your heels and you should feel a pull through your bum and glutes! I'm sure there's lots of vids on YouTube that will help but it shouldn't be sore for you! You did super well-that workout looked tough!! and your mum is v fit!! x
also try to push your knees out as your squat rather than have them collapse inwards, again so you don't hurt yourself x
